com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.enablement

Class SoftwareTypes.CheckType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.vapi.bindings.ApiEnumeration<SoftwareTypes.CheckType>
      • com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.enablement.SoftwareTypes.CheckType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Enclosing interface:
    SoftwareTypes

    public static final class SoftwareTypes.CheckType
extends ApiEnumeration<SoftwareTypes.CheckType>
    The CheckType enumeration class contains various checks to identify the possibility to enable the feature that manages the cluster with a single software specification.

    See enumerated types description.

    • Field Detail

      • SOFTWARE

        public static final SoftwareTypes.CheckType SOFTWARE
        Perform host software check. This check is to report standalone VIBs (VIBs which are not part of any component) and the features on the given cluster that cannot coexist with the feature which manages the cluster with a single software specification.

      • VERSION

        public static final SoftwareTypes.CheckType VERSION
        Perform host version check. This feature does not support hosts with version less than XYZ.

      • STATELESSNESS

        public static final SoftwareTypes.CheckType STATELESSNESS
        Perform host statelessness check. This feature does not support stateless hosts.

      • VUM_REMEDIATION

        public static final SoftwareTypes.CheckType VUM_REMEDIATION
        Perform VUM active remediation check.

      • SOFTWARE_SPECIFICATION_EXISTENCE

        public static final SoftwareTypes.CheckType SOFTWARE_SPECIFICATION_EXISTENCE
        Perform cluster's software specification existence check.

      • VSAN_WITNESS_ELIGIBILITY

        public static final SoftwareTypes.CheckType VSAN_WITNESS_ELIGIBILITY
        Checks to verify if the cluster software specification can be used to manage any vSAN witness hosts in the cluster. This constant field was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.1.
